-- Chinese Airlines to Raise Fuel Surcharges From Today, Business Daily Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-26T23:25:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/chinese-airlines-to-raise-fuel-surcharges-from-today-business-daily-says.html
Air China Ltd., China Southern
Airlines Co. and seven other Chinese carriers will raise
passenger fuel surcharges from today, the National Business
Daily reported, citing a statement from China Southern.  China Southern will charge 70 yuan for flights of more than
800 kilometers, up from 40 yuan, according to the newspaper. The
fee on shorter routes will rise to 40 yuan from 20 yuan,
according to the report.  Air China, China Eastern Airlines Corp. and other domestic
airlines will charge the same amount, according to the
newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  